Mon Jul 18 10:19:15 1994  Yukihiro Matsumoto  (matz@ix-02)

	* parse.y: There was a bug in the rule that handles multiple assignment,
	  which caused failure when assigning more than 3 elements.

	* eval.c(rb_eval): In multiple assignment, when the right-hand side is not
	  an array, convert it to an array using the `to_a' method before assigning.
	  Previously the right-hand value was assigned directly to the first element,
	  but for things like structs that can be converted to arrays, conversion
	  seems nicer.

	* dbm.c,dict.c(delete_if): Added method.

	* process.c(wait,waitpid): When the system call waitpid or wait4 exists,
	  use that. Modified configure to check for them as well.

	* dbm.c, dict.c(clear): Added method.

Fri Jul 15 10:54:45 1994  Yukihiro Matsumoto  (matz@ix-02)

	* array.c(Fary_fill,Fary_clear): Added methods.

	* string.c(Fstr_split): When the value of $; is a 1-character string, split
	  by it as a plain character without converting it to a regular expression.

	* string.c(Fstr_aset/Fstr_aref): Modified the behavior for when the index is
	  outside the string range, referencing Array.

	* array.c(astore,Fary_aset): After reallocating the region, clear it with
	  zero. Until now, garbage remained in arrays.

	* array.c: Cleaned up index handling for []/[]=. Basically, exceptions no
	  longer occur unless assigning to a negative index. Interpret appropriately
	  as needed and expand the region when necessary.

