	* parse.y: Changed the syntax to create arrays to [..]. This breaks
	  compatibility with older Ruby scripts, but introducing syntax for Dict and
	  aligning with perl5 made now the only right time to change it.
	  *BACKWARD INCOMPATIBILITY*

	* eval.c(Feval): When defining methods via eval(), the defined method is now
	  placed in the class to which the method belongs. Previously it was defined
	  in Object.

	* parse.y: Crashed in eval() when no local arguments existed.

